Yes — since the user will **not edit the debit account**, the validation should compare:

```ts
T24 / proposed account = item.accNbr
Debit account = item.sourceAccountNumber
```

If their currencies are different, the row appears in the modal. The edit button still edits only the T24/proposed account number. Your original parent component already uses `accNbr` as the editable proposed account and `sourceAccountNumber` as the debit account, so the rewritten version keeps that structure. 

